Soon after that, they invested in their own equipment to record Ruby Hoedown, and then chronicled their first international conference in Norway in late 2007. Description: INBOX Marketing is a professional services firm specializing in the strategic optimization of email marketing programs.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: INBOX Marketing Inc., an award-winning professional services firm specializing in the strategic optimization of email marketing programs. Responsys Strengthens Leadership Position with Acquisition of INBOX Marketing February 3 2006 Award-Winning Firm Brings Full Complement of Strategic and Tactical Services Expertise to Industry-Leading Email Marketing Solutions Provider  February 3, 2006 â€“ Responsys, a premier provider of on-demand email and lifecycle marketing solutions, today announced the acquisition of INBOX Marketing Inc., an award-winning professional services firm specializing in the strategic optimization of email marketing programs. With this acquisition, Responsys expands the breadth and depth of its professional and account services capabilities to support a rapidly expanding client base of sophisticated, ROI-focused marketers.  For the past five years, INBOX Marketing has sustained a winning track record helping marketers scientifically optimize their customer acquisition, conversion, and retention programs using a unique methodology and a proven set of best practices for strategy, creative, testing, and email program management -- with guaranteed ROI. Based in San Francisco, INBOX Marketing brings to Responsys a team of experienced marketing strategists, interactive designers, campaign developers, and executive management, all of whom will be focused on supporting and expanding Responsys' professional services business.  "INBOX offers an unmatched ability to diagnose, design, and deliver integrated programs that help companies measurably optimize the customer experience across the lifecycle while maximizing every marketing dollar," said Dan Springer, CEO of Responsys. "Building on our shared vision of Individualized Lifecycle Marketing, the INBOX acquisition brings to Responsys greater focus on ensuring customer ROI and an expanded set of capabilities for leveraging the Responsys Interact platform to the fullest. The superior strength of our combined solution further solidifies our leadership position in the email marketing industry."  Responsys was recently cited as a leader in the December 2005 Forrester Wave: Email Marketing Service Providers, Q4 2005, garnering top scores for its customer retention, technology platform, and functionality. This followed on the heels of the company's number one ranking by JupiterResearch in its October 2005 Email Marketing Buyer's Guide. The acquisition of INBOX Marketing strengthens Responsys' position as the largest private and profitable email service provider and builds on its growing recognition as the solution provider of choice for sophisticated email marketers.  "As a full-service firm to leading brands, we have worked with the top email service providers and have seen many struggle to keep pace with the increasingly sophisticated needs of marketers, from both a technical and strategic standpoint," commented former INBOX Marketing President Jerome McLaughlin, now Vice President of Professional Services for Responsys. "The union of our two companies combines the best of both worlds, bringing together innovative marketing technology and world-class strategic marketing services."  As part of the transaction Responsys will maintain the San Francisco office of INBOX Marketing and retain all INBOX employees. The INBOX Marketing executive team will assume leadership roles in the professional services organization at Responsys. Jerome McLaughlin will become Vice President of Professional Services and Barry Stamos will assume the role of Senior Director of Strategy for Responsys.
Industry Groups: Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Professional Services

Full Description: SUMMARY:  PopuTrust, LLC is a SaaS-technology startup business based in Portsmouth, NH. PopuTrust, LLC owns the popular website www.poputrust.com which offers "Trusted People Search" services.  MISSION:  Via its SaaS technology platform (www.poputrust.com) PopuTrust, LLC is focused on becoming the leading source of information about People. With over 10% of all Google searches now "people related" ...people are more and more obsessed with "people".  PopuTrust is the comprehensive & trusted source of aggregated public information. As a "meta-search-engine" PopuTrust allows customers to search at just one location for multiple sources of digital content.     OPPORTUNITY:  People Search is a massive Multi-BILLION dollar market. People no longer just search "for fun" on celebrity names - a quick name search is often a precusor to a business meeting, a romantic date, a landlord/tenant relationship, employer/employee screening, college application process, or other research process.  Billions of Searches for name per DAY from the web (i.e. Google) and increasingly from from Mobile Devices. Currently, big data firms are selling this data to the highest bidder...soon...as awareness of this practice grows...individuals will want to own, control, and sell their personal data back to these same marketers.  PopuTrust is where individuals go to take back control of their Online Identity and sensitive Personal Data.   OUR TEAM: PopuTrust was started by a team of tech entrepreneurs and web software engineers with extensive experience building high growth, profitable ventures including VC-backed SaaS (software-as-a-service) businesses. Their passion for building great internet and "big data" businesses has created an energy and enthusiasm that is infused throughout 8 staff members & contractors onboard including marketing experts, web programmers, SEO gurus, big data compilation experts, and cutting edge web engineers. "Big Data" as it is know has massive technical challenges - as current database technology often cannot keep up with demand. PopuTrust is on the forefront of the "NO-SQL" movement. PopuTrust, LLC was formed and incubated at The Market Accelerator - a startup incubator and technology accelerator based on Market Street in downtown Portsmouth, NH and MIT/ Kendall Square, Cambridge, Mass. Unlike some of the current hiring networks that are focused on contract labor, often for software developers, or high-cost expert-broker firms that use the same small set of opinion leaders, Rerisa enables a broader set of experts to make their knowledge accessible and build their reputation.
